{"name": "socc-plotter", "metadata": {"name": "socc-plotter", "version": "0.5.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["PyQt5", "pyqtgraph", "numpy", "matplotlib", "opencv-python-headless", "PyOpenGL", "qimage2ndarray", "vedo", "pydantic", "pillow", "pyquaternion"], "summary": "Awesome socc_plotter created by AdityaNG", "upload_time": 1733764868}, "documentation": ["# socc_plotter\n\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/branch/main/graph/badge.svg?token=socc_plotter_token_here)](https://codecov.io/gh/AdityaNG/socc_plotter)\n[![CI](https://github.com/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/actions/workflows/main.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/actions/workflows/main.yml)\n[![GitHub License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/AdityaNG/socc_plotter)](https://github.com/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/blob/main/LICENSE)\n[![PyPI - Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/socc_plotter)](https://pypi.org/project/socc_plotter/)\n![PyPI - Downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/socc_plotter)\n\nSemantic Occupancy 3D Plotter. This is the plotter made by the [SOccDPT](https://adityang.github.io/SOccDPT) project to create fancy 3D visuals. You can use this for your own AV or Robotics visualization!\n\n![demo](https://github.com/AdityaNG/socc_plotter/raw/main/media/demo.gif)\n\n## Install it from PyPI\n\n```bash\npip install socc_plotter\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe socc_plotter works on a callback mechanism since the GUI must be run on the main thread.\n```py\nfrom socc_plotter.plotter import Plotter\nimport time\n\ndef callback(plot: Plotter):\n    time.sleep(1)\n    print(\"in callback\")\n    graph_region = plot.graph_region\n\n    points = np.array([[1, 0, 0]])\n    colors = np.array([[1, 1, 1]])\n\n    graph_region.setData(pos=points, color=colors)\n\nplotter = Plotter(\n    callback=callback,\n)\nplotter.start()\n```\n\n\n## NuScenes Demo\n\nStart by downloading the NuScenes mini datset\n```\nmkdir -p data/nuscenes/\ncd data/nuscenes/\nwget -c https://www.nuscenes.org/data/v1.0-mini.tgz\ntar -xf v1.0-mini.tgz\n```\n\nInstall a few dependencies for the demo\n```\npip install nuscenes-devkit==1.1.10\npip install transformers torch torchvision timm accelerate general_navigation\n```\n\nRun the demo\n```bash\n$ python -m socc_plotter\n#or\n$ socc_plotter\n```\n\n## Development\n\nRead the [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) file.\n\n## Cite\n\nCite our work if you find it useful\n\n```bibtex\n@article{NG2024SOccDPT,\n  title={SOccDPT: 3D Semantic Occupancy from Dense Prediction Transformers trained under memory constraints},\n  author={NG, Aditya},\n  journal={Advances in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning},\n  volume={ISSN: 2582-9793, Source Id: 21101164612},\n  year={2024},\n  url={https://www.oajaiml.com/}\n}\n``` \n\n## TODO\n\n- [x] Demo\n    - [x] RGB Frame\n    - [x] Depth perception\n    - [x] Semantic segmentation\n    - [x] NuScenes Calibration\n    - [x] NuScenes Vehicle trajectory\n    - [x] Semantic Occupancy Grid\n- [ ] Ensure demo dependencies are seperate from the module\n- [ ] Demo is to prompt the user to install dependencies\n- [ ] Demo is to auto download NuScenes and unarchive it\n- [ ] Test Cases\n- [ ] PiPy deployment\n"], "modules": [{"name": "socc_plotter.socc_helper", "documentation": ["CLI interface for socc_plotter project.\n\nDemo to run on NuScenes Mini"], "functions": [{"name": "socc_plotter.socc_helper.get_future_vehicle_trajectory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "nusc", "type": {"name": "NuScenes", "xref": {"fqname": "nuscenes.nuscenes.NuScenes", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "current_sample_token", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "future_horizon", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Extracts the future vehicle trajectory starting from a given sample token.\n\n```\nparam nusc\n\nNuScenes object.\n\nparam current_sample_token\n\nToken of the current sample to start from\n\nparam future_horizon\n\nNumber of future time steps to consider.\n\nreturn\n\nA dictionary with vehicle trajectories.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "socc_plotter.socc_helper.depth_to_rgb", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "depth_map", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "socc_plotter.socc_helper.infer_semantics_and_depth", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "nusc", "type": {"name": "NuScenes", "xref": {"fqname": "nuscenes.nuscenes.NuScenes", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sensors", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sample", "type": {"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "current_sample_token", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "dataroot", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "depth_estimator", "type": {"name": "AutoImageProcessor", "xref": {"fqname": "transformers.AutoImageProcessor", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "depth_transform", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "device", "type": {"name": "torch.device", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.device", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "calibration_data", "type": {"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "ty